President Trump presented the Presidential Medal of Freedom to basketball legend Robert Cousy in a ceremony held in the Oval Office. Cousy, known as "Bob," is a beloved figure in the basketball world and has made significant contributions both on and off the court. During his career, he won six NBA championships, was a 13-time NBA All-Star, and was the first NBA player to be featured on the cover of Sports Illustrated. He also played a key role in the establishment of the NBA Players Association and fought for better working conditions and a pension plan for players. Off the court, Cousy has been a passionate advocate for equality and justice. He wrote his senior thesis on the persecution faced by minorities and stood up against racism directed at his teammates. In his acceptance speech, Cousy expressed gratitude for the recognition and reflected on his journey from a challenging childhood to becoming a basketball legend. President Trump praised Cousy's achievements and highlighted his impact both on and off the court.